-- ON THE MOVE-Merrill Lynch hires two advisers from Morgan Stanley
-- 
-- Wed Apr 23, 2014 11:39AM EDT
-- None



April 23 (Reuters) - Bank of America Corp's <BAC.N> Merrill Lynch unit said on Wednesday that it had hired two financial advisers from Morgan Stanley <MS.N>.

Brian Saroken and Gerald Saroken managed about $300 million in assets at Morgan Stanley and had annual fees and commissions in excess of $2.6 million. Brian Saroken joined Merrill Lynch's New York office, while  Gerald Saroken joined the company's White Plains office.